<br>
what im about to say was based on people from other servers, so thought it best to ask my server for the best answer.<br>
<br>
anyway, i seen it posted elsewhere about someone donating 10pp for kei and 20 for virtue. im kind of new to the game, so either people think im really generous, or im indeed giving an &quot;appropriate&quot; amount.<br>
<br>
i usually give 40-50 for kei (100 sometimes - depends on the circumstances), and at least 75 for virtue ( though i dont know about anyone else, i have a hard time finding vitue - settle for temperance  for about 20 usually). i know virtue costs like 30 to cast, so id never give any less that that. <br>
<br>
and please, to be honest, dont say the old &quot;they say casting for donations so any amount is sufficient&quot;, because we all know its really untrue, those casting those mana intensive spells would like to AT LEAST get the money back for the cast, and little bit for the time (not always, but safe to say usually). <br>
<br>
